{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567036","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567036"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:53:19+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:53:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18921"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18921","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18921"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.01,0.01,0.92,0.05]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11654"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80221"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11654","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11654"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18921"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65501"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"19"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5634"},{"type":"tags","id":"5641"},{"type":"tags","id":"5770"},{"type":"tags","id":"8088"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11310"},{"type":"tags","id":"11333"},{"type":"tags","id":"11347"},{"type":"tags","id":"11348"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27409"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27414"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45424"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80221","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/80221"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 42-year-old woman has been diagnosed with early-stage breast cancer. After discussing treatment options with her surgeon, she mentions that she would like to consult another specialist before making a decision about surgery.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate professional response?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Express disappointment in the patient\u0027s lack of confidence","Suggest delaying the second opinion until after the first treatment to avoid treatment delay","Recommend against seeing another specialist to avoid confusion","Provide referral information and offer to share relevant clinical records","Reassure the patient that all relevant options have already been explained thoroughly"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate response is to \u003Cstrong\u003Eprovide referral information and offer to share relevant clinical records\u003C/strong\u003E. This approach supports patient autonomy and demonstrates professional respect for the patient\u0027s right to seek second opinions. It also facilitates informed decision-making and maintains trust in the therapeutic relationship.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect responses are inappropriate because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EExpress disappointment in the patient\u0027s lack of confidence\u003C/strong\u003E is unprofessional and may damage the therapeutic relationship\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESuggest delaying the second opinion until after the first treatment\u003C/strong\u003E undermines the patient\u0027s right to make informed decisions before starting any treatment\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERecommend against seeing another specialist\u003C/strong\u003E fails to respect patient autonomy and is a paternalistic approach to medical care\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReassure the patient that all relevant options have already been explained thoroughly\u003C/strong\u003E dismisses the patient\u0027s wishes and could be interpreted as defensive or controlling behaviour\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESupporting a patient\u0027s right to seek second opinions is an essential component of good medical practice and helps maintain high standards of professional conduct. It demonstrates respect for patient autonomy and shared decision-making principles.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Medical practitioners have an ethical obligation to support patients seeking second opinions as part of good medical practice.","Supporting second opinions demonstrates respect for patient autonomy and shared decision-making.","A professional response to requests for second opinions helps maintain trust in the therapeutic relationship."],"references":["Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 15]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65501"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18921"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"65501","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/65501"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-18T11:57:37+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-18T11:59:57+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11654"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"80221"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"19","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/19"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udd2a","name":"General Surgery","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:47:20+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"2"}}},"meta